    "name": "COU1: Non-cannulated construct compression-bending prediction",
    "description": "FEA predicts construct stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement for the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw design under ASTM F1717 static compression-bending. Validated by direct comparison to bench testing (N=11 constructs across two laboratories). Model influence MEDIUM (testing confirms results); decision consequence MEDIUM (pedicle screw fracture leads to revision surgery, not death).",
    "intendedUse": "Demonstrate that the FEA modeling framework reproduces experimental compression-bending behavior of a non-cannulated pedicle screw construct within pre-established acceptance bounds (<10% QoI difference, E/uval < 1.96).",
    "modelInfluence": "Medium",
    "decisionConsequence": "Medium",
    "deviceClass": "Class II",
    "hasOperatingEnvelope": {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/cou/cou1-noncannulated/operating-envelope",
      "type": "OperatingEnvelope",
      "name": "ASTM F1717 compression-bending operating envelope for 7.5 mm non-cannulated pedicle screw",
      "description": "Axial compressive load range: 0–2500 N applied at crosshead displacement rate 5 mm/min ± 0.5 mm/min. Screw outer diameter: 7.5 mm ± 0.05 mm. Screw length: 45 mm ± 1 mm. Construct offset distance: 44 mm per ASTM F1717 fixture. Titanium alloy Ti-6Al-4V ELI; elastic modulus 114 GPa ± 3 GPa; yield strength 795 MPa ± 20 MPa. Test temperature: 23 °C ± 2 °C. All 11 validation constructs fall within these bounds; no extrapolation beyond envelope is claimed."
    },
    "hasApplicabilityConstraint": {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/cou/cou1-noncannulated/applicability-constraint",
      "type": "ApplicabilityConstraint",
      "name": "Applicability constraint: non-cannulated 7.5 mm Ti-6Al-4V pedicle screw under quasi-static F1717 loading",
      "description": "Model applicability is restricted to non-cannulated pedicle screws with outer diameter 7.0–8.0 mm, constructed from Ti-6Al-4V ELI, subjected to quasi-static (crosshead rate ≤ 10 mm/min) compression-bending per ASTM F1717. Cannulated designs, dynamic fatigue loading, and alternative alloys (CoCr, stainless steel) are explicitly out of scope. Spinal level is limited to thoracolumbar (T10–L5) where standard 44 mm offset fixture geometry applies."
    }
  },
  "hasSensitivityAnalysis": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/sensitivity/noncannulated-sa-001",
    "type": "SensitivityAnalysis",
    "name": "Sensitivity analysis: elastic modulus and contact friction coefficient effects on QoI",
    "description": "Ti-6Al-4V elastic modulus was varied ±5% (108–120 GPa) and screw-rod contact friction coefficient was varied from 0.15 to 0.35; construct stiffness QoI changed by less than 3.2% and yield force by less than 2.8% across the full parameter space, confirming that model predictions are insensitive to plausible material property uncertainty within the declared operating envelope."
  },
